cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about a morphological learner program that takes a POS-tagged lexicon as input and generates new words beyond the learning sample. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the program uses unsupervised learning to induce morphological relationships without attempting to discover or identify morphemes. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the program uses AI techniques to generate new words. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category as there is no mention of neural networks or evolutionary algorithms in the paper. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is the least likely category as the paper does not focus on sound or speech processing.
